<span class=title> play with percentages</span><hr size=1> Maybe because the poorest 50% don't own 50%, or even 25% of the nation's wealth?  Come on, Meddik, you took math for engineers, you should know well enough that the figure doesn't mean anything when the richest 5% of families own 60% of the wealth.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 8:26:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: play with percentages</span><hr size=1> I think what Meddik wants may be a flat tax, because, after all, a flat tax is fair.<br>
<br>
So...  here is Swipey's flat tax plan<br>
<br>
Take all the budget outlays for the country (about 1.6 trillion in the year i have data for (1995)) and devide by the number of people in the country (about 280 million).  Viola!  a truly fair flat tax.  No coddling the poor or the unemployed.  Everyone owes about $5300.  If you don't have a job, the government extracts the value of your taxes from you in labor.  Or, if you dont have a job and are a dependent of someone else (such as if you are a child) your guardian is responsible for your share, and again, if they cant come up with it, are liable for extraction.<br>
<br>
I, for one, am tired of subsidizing other people's reproduction and laziness.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulilum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 1:20:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: play with percentages</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah someone is poor so they are obviously lazy.  <br>
